import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    group_counts = data['group'].value_counts()
    group_counts.plot(kind='bar', color=['blue', 'green', 'red'])
    plt.xlabel('Group')
    plt.ylabel('Count of Persons')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of persons across different groups?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=0)
    plt.legend(['Group 1', 'Group 2', 'Group 3'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
from wordcloud import WordCloud

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    names = data['person'].tolist()
    text = ' '.join(names)
    wordcloud = WordCloud(width=800, height=400, background_color='white', colormap='viridis').generate(text)
    
    plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')
    plt.axis("off")
    plt.title("What is the most common name among all persons?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    group_sizes = data.groupby('group').size().reset_index(name='count')
    plt.bar(group_sizes['group'], group_sizes['count'])
    plt.xlabel('Group')
    plt.ylabel('Count of Persons')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of group sizes?')
    plt.xticks(group_sizes['group'])
    plt.legend(['Group Sizes'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Group by 'group' and count the number of persons in each group
    group_counts = data.groupby('group')['person'].count().reset_index()
    group_counts.columns = ['group', 'count']

    # Create a box plot of the count of persons in each group
    sns.boxplot(x='group', y='count', data=group_counts)
    plt.title("What is the average number of persons in each group?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Group")
    plt.ylabel("Count of Persons")
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    group_counts = data['group'].value_counts()
    plt.pie(group_counts, labels=group_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of group IDs?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(group_counts.index, title="Group IDs", loc="upper right")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
